Visit www.epic-contests.com and find the Chiller's Getaway on the platform. Enter by submitting a piece of content (photo/video) of yourself. Then you have to earn the highest number of credits by either taking the quiz, using promo codes from our social media platforms or by purchasing credits. There is a live leaderboard on the platform that shows you in real time, who is leading the contest. The king himself, Stogie T will bring the show to sub-zero temperatures as he shows off his rap prowess that comes with a 15-year strong repertoire of skill, effortless cool and unmatched lyricism all from the comfort of his home.

We also discuss the blessers of the country, the Oppenheimer and Rupert family for their generous donation to assist small business during these trying times, a fair donation or looking after their interest? We give a shout out to the team that work tirelessly behind the scenes to make sure your fix of the pod is delivered fresh and as you want it. All that and more on another episode of your favorite podcast and a big shout out to all our subscribers in these trying times.

items.content: We are back in these trying times of COVID -19 and fear not because Ghost Lady has enough sanitizer to keep us safe and there is only three of us minus Thabang. The DStv Mzansi Viewers' Choice Awards took place and we look at how Mzansi handles red carpet events. What are the dos and donts of braais since we are going to be doing a lot of those but keeping it to under a 100 people. Plus we look at who is celebrity enough in Mzansi - who are A -List celebs, share your thought LIKE and COMMENT and SUBSCRIBE to SA's Number One Podcast

items.content: Wanda Mkhize has worked within the strategy field in both the private and public sector for over 15 years. This experience stretches across financial, broadcasting telecommunications and esports industry. She has both consulting and operational experience in business turnaround strategy development and implementation; development of new operating models, product development; DTT Content Strategy; Funding strategy development and acquisition

Tracy Ziman Jacobs qualified Social Worker and Intimacy Coach who is passionate about assisting couples and individuals wishing to transcend another level of intimacy within their relationships.



Having graduated in 1996 with a BA (Social Science) I attended Family Life Centre (FAMSA) for the duration of my practical training and thereafter was employed at Family Life Center as an Occupational Social Worker.

items.content: New week means another episode of your favourite podcast. The Mabenas are home alone this week as the Ghost Lady is feeling a little bit under the weather but show must go on. This week we look at some of the suggestion emails sent through by you the chillers on how to make your fav even better than it already is. What is ASMR - we look it the soothing sounds it makes and if it can make you fall asleep. A Reece, is he the best we have in the country and can we name him the SA Jay Z, the gloves are off the gents have a say on the matter plus Patrice Motsepe goes big with banking and yes Thabang is in the house once again. Another fire Podcast and Chill with MacG episode.

items.content: this week get to chill with Rikhado Makhado , professionally known as Riky Rick.A South African rapper, songwriter and actor. He is known for his style and his love for the local fashion scene and is the founder "Cotton Club Records". Makhado rose to fame when he released his single "Nafukwa". He is also known for being a member of the trendsetting crew Boyz N Bucks.

items.content: Another episode of Podcast and Chill is here and more relevant than most music awards ceremonies. Speaking of which, are they still a thing? The team break down the interest people have in award ceremonies. Mabena has Premium now and he hints at watching The River has people shedding a tears. We celebrate the life of Kobe Bryant after news of his tragic passing plus Kabza and Maphorisa manage to sneak in again. The Queen of Gqom and head honcho of West Ink, are they okay - we give our views on that and a host of other topics on another fire episode of your favorite podcast.

items.content: Check out the latest episode of Podcast & Chill with MacG as we look into music groups in the Mzansi, are they still a thing. The story is finally told and on that note - do you have a story about the “weirdest” chiller you ever come across. School woes - we all have stories to tell about our time in primary school and high school, the team shares their experiences plus we ain’t wearing no yellow bibs but we look into population dynamics in this country - who do you think is an endangered species, find that out and a whole lot more from your favs - Podcast & Chill with MacG

items.content: Motshidisi Mohono is an award winning Sport Broadcaster – currently plying her trade at SuperSport International and Vision View Sports Radio. She was recently named Journalist of the Year at the 2018 SA Sport Awards – the first woman in the history of the awards to receive the coveted nod. Her stellar work, that garnered the win, included being part of SuperSport’s production team for the England tour to South Africa; anchoring Super Rugby games in studio and travelling to New Zealand to cover the tournament’s final.

items.content: The king of podcasts is back like he never left. They are even woke woke, infact what is being woke? A friend of the show and a former ghost lady Penny joins us and you know she has stories to tell for days. Series is a way of life and we look into the much talked about Netflix Original, #TheMessiah. New year, new me blah blah blah, Lenn'yonce claims to run rings around his complex, a lousy couple of meters, n*** please. We also try to share a little enLIGHTenment with the power situation via Eishkom because, ya no, we are seeing flames not light. All this and more on your favourite podcast, PODCAST & CHILL WITH MACG.

items.content:
Our first Interview of 2020 features the beautiful and talented Candice Modiselle



Candice Modiselle is a South African actress and presenter best known for her role as Lerato on the SABC1 soap opera Generations: The Legacy. She was previously known as a presenter on the kids show YOTV Live, on SABC1.The sister of entertainers Bontle Modiselle and Refilwe Modiselle, Candice studied Drama as a high school subject from Grade 10 to Matric at McAuley House Convent in Parktown, Johannesburg.She was one of six finalists in the ACT DALRO performance scholarship competition 2012 and she graduated from the University of Witwatersrand in 2017 with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Dramatic Arts (Honours).Candice landed a presenting gig on YOTV Live in June 2016, spending two years on the show before leaving in June 2018.During her time on YOTV she landed the recurring role of Lerato on the SABC1 soapie Generations: The Legacy, making her first appearance on 12 January, 2017.She was also a guest presenter on the SABC1 music shows Live AMP and Selimathunzi in 2018.Candice was one of four celebrities who were featured on the first episode of the fifth season of the BBC Brit reality series Come Dine With Me South Africa, a celebrity special which aired on 11 March, 2019.In 2019 she landed her first starring role in television in the 1Magic / Mzansi Magic drama series Impilo (The Scam)

Candice Modiselle is a South African actress and presenter best known for her role as Lerato on the SABC1 soap opera Generations: The Legacy. She was previously known as a presenter on the kids show YOTV Live, on SABC1.The sister of entertainers Bontle Modiselle and Refilwe Modiselle, Candice studied Drama as a high school subject from Grade 10 to Matric at McAuley House Convent in Parktown, Johannesburg.She was one of six finalists in the ACT DALRO performance scholarship competition 2012 and she graduated from the University of Witwatersrand in 2017 with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Dramatic Arts (Honours).Candice landed a presenting gig on YOTV Live in June 2016, spending two years on the show before leaving in June 2018.During her time on YOTV she landed the recurring role of Lerato on the SABC1 soapie Generations: The Legacy, making her first appearance on 12 January, 2017.She was also a guest presenter on the SABC1 music shows Live AMP and Selimathunzi in 2018.Candice was one of four celebrities who were featured on the first episode of the fifth season of the BBC Brit reality series Come Dine With Me South Africa, a celebrity special which aired on 11 March, 2019.In 2019 she landed her first starring role in television in the 1Magic / Mzansi Magic drama series Impilo (The Scam)

And we attempt to find out how initiation schools can contribute positive change to raise more responsible men but Mabena and Mabena go south. Only on Podcast and Chill
